<title>ITALY: Italian retail sales rose 1.6 pct in Jan yr/yr.</title>
<headline>Italian retail sales rose 1.6 pct in Jan yr/yr.</headline>
<dateline>ROME 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Retail sales of medium and large firms in Italy rose 1.6 percent in January 1997 compared with a year earlier, according to calculations with a new base of 1995=100, national statistics institute ISTAT said.</p>
<p>The previous base was 1990=100.</p>
<p>Istat said the new retail sales index was 91.7 against 90.3 in the same year in 1996.</p>
<p>Istat said the data referred to the current value of sales and therefore showed the trend of quantity as well as price.</p>
<p>-- Rome newsroom +396 678 2501</p>
